cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms to evolve programs for playing Atari games. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper involves training programs to play games. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper involves developing intelligent agents to play Atari games. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is relevant as the function set used in the evolved programs includes image processing operations. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves developing strategies for playing games.
